From dbb090590c88f397fbe6c409d562dd7c3b17e3a5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gautham Kumar Senthilkumaran <gauthamk@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 25 Jul 2025 22:06:24 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:CP: wifi:ath11k: Avoid ath11k radio access during
 regulatory channel update

During the regulatory channel update scenario, radio does not have
proper pdevs allocated during that instance. So, during this channel
update when we try to take the ath11k radio, it goes for crash as
there is no NULL check by returning error value.

This ath11k radio is not required for channel update, this is taken
for checking the vdev type. Even in the working case everytime ath11k
radio returns invalid vdev type which is not required for channel
update.

Channel update is happening in the default regulatory of ath11k base
everytime and this vdev type is not required for regulatory channel
update.

Signed-off-by: Gautham Kumar Senthilkumaran <gauthamk@qti.qualcomm.com>

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/reg.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/reg.c
index a7d6bf7..b050dd4 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/reg.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/reg.c
@@ -876,6 +876,9 @@ static enum wmi_vdev_type ath11k_reg_get_ar_vdev_type(struct ath11k *ar)
 {
 	struct ath11k_vif *arvif;
 
+	if (!ar)
+		return WMI_VDEV_TYPE_UNSPEC;
+
 	/* Currently each struct ath11k maps to one struct ieee80211_hw/wiphy
 	 * and one struct ieee80211_regdomain, so it could only store one group
 	 * reg rules. It means multi-interface concurrency in the same ath11k is
-- 
2.34.1

